# Method

## Participants

`r n_participants` participants completed the experiment: `r n_l1` L1 Spanish speakers and `r n_l2` L2 Spanish learners.

## Procedure

Three-phase Spanish stress-suffix association task in PsychoPy: pre-test (360 trials, 6 blocks), training (120 trials with feedback), post-test (360 trials, parallel structure). On each trial, participants heard a spoken stimulus and selected *PRESENTE* or *PASADO*.

Pre/post stimuli were drawn from six conditions varying in verb stress (paroxytone, oxytone), noun match (Match, Mismatch), and verb match (Match, Mismatch). Training stimuli were two conditions: `parox` (a) and `oxy` (b).

```{r legend-table}
kable(cond_legend_prepost,
      caption = "Table 1. Condition coding for pre- and post-test stimuli.",
      col.names = c("Cond", "Name", "Verb stress", "Verb match", "Suffix tense", "Noun match", "Splice"),
      align = c("c", "l", "l", "l", "l", "l", "c"))
```

```{r legend-table-train}
kable(cond_legend_training,
      caption = "Table 2. Condition coding for training stimuli.",
      col.names = c("Cond", "Name", "Verb stress", "Tense"),
      align = c("c", "l", "l", "l"))
```

## Analysis

Reaction time was analyzed on correct trials, incorrect trials, and all trials, with bounds 200–5000 ms. Group means were computed by averaging within participant first, then across participants.

Inferential analyses were run with generalized linear mixed-effects models (`lme4`) following Casillas (2025). Accuracy was modeled with a binomial-logit family; reaction time was modeled with a Gaussian family on 1/RT (reciprocal transformation; Box-Cox optimum λ ≈ −0.7, 95% CI [−0.8, −0.6]). All categorical predictors used sum contrasts. Random effects: by-participant intercepts and slopes for phase, by-item intercepts. Effects were tested via nested model comparisons. Predicted values are back-transformed (probabilities for accuracy, ms for RT).

In sum-coded factor tables, condition labels use the format `stress / N± / V±` where `N+/V+` = match and `N−/V−` = mismatch. The reference cell (not shown in tables) is `oxy / N+ / V−`; its β equals the negative sum of the other five coefficients.

